As always match Ts and Cs always

00:45:18.000 --> 00:45:22.000
match Gs, each strand has
enough information for the other.

00:45:22.000 --> 00:45:27.000
That's how replication happens.
You have two strands, each of which

00:45:27.000 --> 00:45:32.000
has sufficient information
to encode the other.

00:45:32.000 --> 00:45:35.000
They somehow come apart. They
each serve as a template for

00:45:35.000 --> 00:45:38.000
the other. And that's that.
That is the secret of life, how

00:45:38.000 --> 00:45:41.000
