00:50:32.000 --> 00:50:35.000
And depending on where the DNA
migrated, you could measure the

00:50:35.000 --> 00:50:38.000
density of the DNA. And
they were able to show that,

00:50:38.000 --> 00:50:41.000
in fact, newly replicated DNA
strands had this intermediate

00:50:41.000 --> 00:50:45.000
density that would be expected
from the semi-conservative model.

00:50:45.000 --> 00:50:48.000
And so, in fact, by that point
the semi-conservative model,

00:50:48.000 --> 00:50:51.000
I think, is well established.
In some sense you would say the

00:50:51.000 --> 00:50:55.000
